<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 6:12PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Widespread light to moderate snow will persist this evening.
* Snowfall rates between a quarter-inch to three-quarter inch
will be likely through 8 PM. Some mixing in of rain will be
possible, particularly through the Metro region and along or
south of I-94, closer to 8 PM.
* East-southeast winds around 20 to 25 mph with gusts 35 mph.
Highly fluctuating visibilities down to a half-mile are
expected given the breezy conditions and moderate snow rates.
* Temperatures range between 32 to 34 degrees F.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow will lead to slippery roads, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Moderate snow will bring a reduction in visibility down to a
half-mile at times.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
